titleStmt.title: A catologue of the names of such persons as did actually sit as judges upon the tryall of Charles the First, with councel and attendants of the court. Whereunto is added, the names of the lord mayor and aldermen of the city of London, that personally proclaimed the act for abolishing kingly government..

notesStmt.note: Lists Oliver Cromwell, Lieu. Generall [and 105 other names].
Reproduction of original in the British Library.
